The paper deals with a system of synchronous processes that communicate by sending messages to each other, and must perform a certain amount of work while tolerating process failures. This suggests that the paper belongs to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the number of messages sent, the total amount of work performed, and time complexity, which are all relevant to the Distributed Systems (cs.DS) sub-category. The paper also deals with fault tolerance, which is a topic in the Distributed Computing (cs.Distributed) sub-category. The paper discusses the possibility of process failures, which suggests that it may also belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the time complexity of the protocols, which suggests that it may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
